originalText.text: I want to clarify that the situation at this site isn't fair to the nurses. They are checking in people and taking the tests all by themselves. That is why it takes so long, they are doing their best, and there are only two of them. I never got my rapid test results, and I see on the reviews, that is the case for many other people. So I am sure it is not the nurse's fault. Whoever is behind the logistics of this site they are setting the nurses up to fail. Avoid this site and take your test on a city MD or Urgent Care facility. I hope the nurses are getting fair compensation.

originalText.text: I went for a rapid test on 12/19/21 at 4pm. "The results will be emailed to you in 20 minutes"...18 hours later no email.  Do not go their if you made flight plans or need for work.

originalText.text:
This place is on the corner of my job so it is convenient. They have a new system where you sign up, after you make line, for a 5 min interval appointment. Like this you do not have to wait on a line for hours.

The staff is friendly and helpful. the only thing is that for a rapid test, results should be available within 15-20 mins. And for the most part, I have to call or swing by to get my results b/c they forget to email them to you.

originalText.text: The most inefficient site with incredibly poor customer service.  Not sure if all staff are like this but on January 3rd it was miserable.

originalText.text: Not even one star. I got my COVID test done in August at 80 Carmine St. I was told I would get email results in 2 hours. I had to chase down the number and  call after it did not come. I was lucky that someone (from another location) picked up after multiple rings. I was told verbally that I was "negative" but 24 hours later, I have no email confirmation. Now there is no answer when I call. They do not even have a website. These people are sanctioned by NYC Health? Typical DeBlasio slop...
